'Just some crazy person who wanted something they had.'

Jose Tamayo, a gardener who was working nearby, reported seeing a man exit the property minutes before the incident was discovered, reports San Gabriel Valley Tribune. 

Tamayo said the man was wearing a green jacket with a hood, a baseball cap and jeans. He said the man picked up a backpack from nearby bushes, put it on and walked away. 

According to neighbors, Mr Isom had been in construction for many years. 

The pair are believed to have had children and grandchildren.  

